{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/10673", "repo": "rails", "body": "That's a good point on Decorators. I'm not sure that there's any way to handle that with the method it's using, now.\r\n\r\nThe only reason I didn't go to using an instance method straight away is because it'd require monkey patching several core classes. Especially since this would require patching BasicObject, it makes me feel a bit uncomfortable. That said, I'm not opposed to doing it that way if that's not a huge concern.", "_id": {"$oid": "523cc514bd354364b90025e9"}, "issue_id": 10673, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/18152126", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/10673#issuecomment-18152126", "updated_at": "2013-05-20T15:02:39Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif", "login": "sgrif", "gravatar_id": "0f674817f8c6e149518f0a4b4ad3d560", "html_url": "https://github.com/sgrif", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/0f674817f8c6e149518f0a4b4ad3d560?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F7f844d9af6961157c094f8d5bbf716a0.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1529387, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sgrif/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2013-05-20T15:02:39Z", "id": 18152126, "owner": "rails"}
